# Architecture

## Data flow

```
Browser → middleware.ts (JWT cookie) → App Router page OR API route
                                              ↓
                                    src/lib/* (auth, documents, validation)
                                              ↓
                                    src/lib/prisma.ts → Prisma → SQLite
```

Client components call `/api/*` via `fetch`; server pages may call `prisma` directly.

## Layer boundaries

| Layer | Path | Does | Must NOT |
|-------|------|------|----------|
| Middleware | `src/middleware.ts` | JWT gate, redirect unauthenticated | DB queries, business rules |
| API routes | `src/app/api/**/route.ts` | Auth check, Zod validate, HTTP status | TipTap/UI logic, direct cookie writes except via `lib/auth` |
| Server pages | `src/app/**/page.tsx` | SSR data fetch, pass props to client | Client-only APIs (`useState` without `"use client"`) |
| Client components | `src/components/**` | UI, `fetch` to API, TipTap | Direct `prisma` import |
| Domain lib | `src/lib/**` | Auth, access rules, validation, TipTap extensions | `NextResponse`, JSX |
| DB | `prisma/schema.prisma` | Schema, relations | Application logic |

## Imports

```typescript
// ✅ API route
import { getSession } from "@/lib/auth";
import { getDocumentAccess } from "@/lib/documents";
import { prisma } from "@/lib/prisma";

// ❌ Client component
import { prisma } from "@/lib/prisma";

// ❌ lib layer
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
```

## DI / wiring

- **Prisma**: singleton in `src/lib/prisma.ts` (dev hot-reload safe)
- **Auth**: `getSession()` / `createSession()` from `src/lib/auth.ts` — no global user context
- **Env**: `JWT_SECRET`, `DATABASE_URL` via `process.env`; never hard-code secrets

## Directory tree

```
src/app/           Routes (pages + API)
src/components/    React UI; ribbon/ = Word toolbar
src/lib/           Domain + auth + validation + tiptap/
src/middleware.ts  Auth gate
prisma/            schema.prisma, seed.ts
```

## Hard constraints

- Every API route: `getSession()` first → 401 if missing
- Document access: use `getDocumentAccess()` / `isDocumentOwner()` — never roll custom checks
- Validate all request bodies with Zod schemas from `src/lib/validation.ts`
- TipTap editor: client-only via `DocumentEditorLoader` (`dynamic`, `ssr: false`)
- `"use client"` only where hooks/events/browser APIs are required
- SQLite local; production needs Turso/libSQL — do not assume file DB on Vercel
